課程大綱




為確保您我的權利,請尊重智慧財產權及不得非法影印




課程概述
本課程將從本土及全球觀點檢視當代健康政策議題。整個學期課程分三部分：第一部分探討基本議題，包括人口轉型、流行病學轉型，以及人人健康運動；第二部分討論重要公共衛生策略，包括基本醫療保健服務、非傳染性疾病防治全球行動計畫、全民健保、健康服務研究，以及健康主流化；第三部分為審慎閱讀至少三本最新國際組織（如世界衛生組織年報、國際兒童基金會或世界銀行）或重要國家（如美國、英國或加拿大）出版之健康政策報告。 This course aims to examine current health policy issues from both local and global perspectives. The course consists of three parts. The first part presents fundamental issues, including demographic transition, epidemiological transition, and health for all movement. The second part discusses essential public health strategies to achieve health for all, including primary health care, global action plan for non-communicable disease prevention, universal health coverage, health services research, and health in all policies. The third part critically evaluates at least three newly issued key health policy reports from major international organizations (e.g., WHO, UNICEF, World Bank) and from selected countries (e.g., USA, UK, Canada).  


課程目標
在學期結束時，選課學生能做到：- 闡述一些健康政策的基本概念；- 說明追求人人健康的有效公共衛生策略；以及 - 確認一些近期全球重要的健康政策議題。 At the end of this course students should be able to:- describe basic concepts of health policy;- illustrate effective public health strategies for achieving health for all; and- identify most recent global health policy issues. 


課程要求
This course meets for two hours, once a week and is conducted mainly as a participatory seminar. Students are expected to read all required readings and prepare a short critique before the class. Each student is required to present and lead the discussion on one tackling strategy in the second part of the course. There will be a 10-15 pages project report, due June 17, 2014. Students are to be graded according to their performance in short critique (20%), class discussion (30%), and project report (50%). 


Office Hours
